tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated HbA1c, indicating impaired glucose control or possible diabetes. Creatinine is slightly elevated, suggesting possible mild renal impairment. Chloride is high and total CO₂ is low, which may indicate a mild metabolic acidosis. Other parameters are within normal limits. Correlation with clinical findings and further evaluation of renal function and acid-base status are recommended.
